<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> with a large moulded capital which is damaged (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.61</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.02</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.66</measure>: capital, width lost x <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.27</measure>).</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face. </p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.055-0.06</measure>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date cert="low" exact="both" notAfter="0138" notBefore="0117">A.D. 117-138</date>
(<rs type="criteria">reign</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor"><w>Αὐτοκράτο<lb n="2" type="worddiv"/>ρα</w>  <name reg="Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρα</name>    <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="3"/> <persName type="emperor"><w lemma="θεός">θεοῦ</w> <name reg="Τραιανός">Τραια<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="4" type="worddiv"/>νοῦ</name>  <name reg="Παρθικός">Παρθι<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>κοῦ</name> <add place="overstrike"><w lemma="υἱός">υἱὸν</w></add> <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><w lemma="θεός">θεοῦ</w>  <lb n="6"/><name reg="Νέρβα">Νέρουα</name></persName></persName> <w>υἱω<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="7" type="worddiv"/>νὸν</w>  <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><name reg="Τραιανός">Τραια<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="8" type="worddiv"/>νον</name>  <name reg="Ἁδριανός">Ἁδρια<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="9" type="worddiv"/>νὸν</name>  <w lemma="σεβαστός">Σεβασ<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="10" type="worddiv"/>τὸν</w></persName></persName>  <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w>  <w>Δῆμος</w></ab>
</div>

<div type="apparatus">
<head>Apparatus</head>
<p>l. 5, <foreign lang="grc">ΥΙΟΝ</foreign> cut over <foreign lang="grc">ΥΙΩ</foreign></p>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Imperator Caesar Trajanus Hadrianus Augustus, son of (the) god Trajanus conqueror of the Parthians, grandson of (the) god Nerva. The People (put up his statue).</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>This base is approximately a pair with <xref type="iAph">1311</xref> (=77.34) (dedication to Nerva). A further dedication from the same building, to Antoninus Pius (<xref type="iAph">1300</xref>=80.24) is a little different in style. Were all these among the <foreign lang="grc">τειμαὶ Σεβαστῶν</foreign> claimed by Diogenes, who built the gate? If so, he was precipitate in claiming to have dedicated them. Should the Nerva be taken to be as late as the latest in the group? If so, which—Antoninus Pius?</p>
</div>
